	(916, 'Senior Accounts Executive/Assistant Accountant (Full Sets)', '/en/job/493407/senior-accounts-executiveassistant-accountant-full-sets', 'Finance', '2023-12-31 07:55:00', 'Diploma in Accountancy or equivalent\nMinimum 2 years of relevant working experience.\nWorking knowledge of Singapore Financial Reporting Standards\nPrior experience in process development projects would be advantageous\nWorking knowledge of Singapore Financial Reporting Standards\nMeticulous and able to work independently\nGood team player with strong interpersonal and communication skills.'),
	(917, 'Inventory Planner', '/en/job/493405/inventory-planner', 'Engineering', '2023-12-31 07:55:00', 'Requirements and skills:\nNITEC in any discipline\nProficient in Microsoft office applications like Excel and Word \nPreferably with previous experience as an inventory planner or in a similar role\nPreferably with experience in Maximo and/or Oracle Fusion'),
	(918, 'BIM Modeller', '/en/job/493404/bim-modeller', 'Engineering', '2023-12-31 07:55:00', 'Diploma in either Civil Engineering, Sustainable Urban Design & Engineering, Construction Engineering, Architecture or equivalent; or BCA Specialist Diploma in Building Information Modelling\nCompetent in AutoCAD 2D/3D and Revit\nKnowledge of e-BIM submission system\nPreferably with at least 3 years of working experience as BIM Modeller/Co-ordinator for infrastructure works and sub-utilities like drainage/sewerage'),
	(919, 'Senior Programmer Analyst / Systems Analyst / Assistant Manager (Port+)', '/en/job/493367/senior-programmer-analyst-systems-analyst-assistant-manager-port', 'Operations', '2023-12-31 07:55:00', 'Diploma or Bachelor  degree in Information System, Computer Science or related\nProven experience of one or more: Java, .NET, Angular, Spring Boot and relational databases (MS SQL, My SQL, Oracle)\nMinimum 2 years of working experience in software development, implementations and support\nKnowledge of software best practices, like Test-Driven Development (TDD) and Continuous Integration/Continuous Delivery (CI/CD)\nAble to work independently and in a team environment\nGood technical acumen\nHighly conscientious, strong analytical and problem-solving skills\nFast learner, able to multi-task and self-motivated to keep up to date with new technologies and business solutioning\nAdaptability and Resilience at work. Responsible and able to work under pressure and within timeline in a dynamic environment\nGood communication and interpersonal skills'),
	(920, 'Assistant Management Executive (Shared Services)', '/en/job/493400/assistant-management-executive-shared-services', 'Admin', '2023-10-31 07:55:00', 'Possess Diploma qualifications\nGood organization and time management skills\nAble to multi-task and work as a team player\nSelf-motivated, meticulous and willing to learn\nFluent in English, able to communicate with individuals at all levels in the organization\nProficient in Microsoft Office (Outlook, Word, Excel and Powerpoint'),
	(921, 'Senior/Principal Electrical Engineer (Energy Infrastructure)', '/en/job/493401/seniorprincipal-electrical-engineer-energy-infrastructure', 'Engineering', '2023-12-31 07:55:00', 'Degree in Electrical Engineering at least 5 years of relevant experience\nStrong knowledge of, and hands-on experience in, the design and/or maintenance of electrical building services\nFamiliar with local Code of Practices, Building and Fire Safety Regulations\nWilling to work outdoors\nThose who had completed the  igh voltage operation for engineers course will have an advantage'),
	(922, 'Deputy Manager / Manager (Green Mobility)', '/en/job/493402/deputy-manager-manager-green-mobility', 'Engineering', '2023-12-31 07:55:00', 'Degree in Electrical Engineering, Chemical Engineering, or a related field\nDeep understanding of battery chemistry, electrochemical processes, and cell design, preferably with experience in various battery chemistries (eg lithium-ion, solid-state, flow batteries)\nStrong knowledge of battery application (eg electric mobility and energy storage technologies) and lifecycle management (eg 2nd life reuse and recycling) including state of health monitoring\nExperience in battery design, modeling, testing and validation\nProficiency in battery management systems, electrical circuit design and simulation tools\nFamiliarity with industry standards and regulations related to battery safety, performance and 2nd life reuse\nExcellent problem-solving skills and ability to work in a collaborative team environment\nStrong communication skills to convey technical concepts effectively'),
	(923, 'Deputy Manager (Sustainability)', '/en/job/493399/deputy-manager-sustainability', 'Engineering', '2023-12-31 07:55:00', 'A degree in Engineering or a Science-based discipline\nRelated working experience\nPassionate about sustainability and a green future\nGood skills in idea conceptualization, communications, analysis and problem solving'),
	(924, 'Manager / Senior Manager  IT Security Governance', '/en/job/493073/manager-senior-manager-it-security-governance', 'Infocomm Technology', '2023-10-31 07:55:00', ' Bachelor  degree in Computer/Electrical/Electronics Engineering or Computer Science, preferably with industry recognized security certification such as CISSP, CRISC, CISM, etc. At least 3 years (5 years for senior manager position) of experience in IT security governance role (preferably in CII environment). Cloud Computing, Risk Assessment (Advantages) Strong problem solving and analytical skills Excellent verbal and written communication skills and customer service skills Ability to thrive under pressure, function and deliver effectively in a fast-paced environment'),
	(925, 'DevOps Engineer', '/en/job/493394/devops-engineer', '', '2023-09-30 07:55:00', ' Degree in Computing, Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Information Systems or equivalent Able to work independently; set and meet challenging personal targets; good communication skills Proficient in linux or windows scripting Strong analytical and problem-solving skills Highly conscientious, meticulous and able to multi-task Be prepared to work in a team providing 24x7 system support\nThe following will be highly valued: Knowledge in DevOps Methodologies like CI/CD, automation tools, building tools (Gradle, MSBuild) Proficient in programming (C, C#, C++, JAVA) and relational databases and related scripting (Oracle,SQL) Knowledge of software best practices, like Test-Driven Development (TDD) and Continuous Integration (CI) At least 3 years of relevant working experience\nOnly shortlisted candidates will be notified'),
	(926, 'Manager (ChemCare)', '/en/job/493391/manager-chemcare', 'Operations', '2023-12-31 07:55:00', '5-10 years of direct work experience in Logistics/Transportation or Supply Chain, Chemical background is preferable\nBachelor  degree in chemical related field.'),
	(927, 'Port+ Supervisor/ Assistant Port+ Executive (Warehouse/ Freight) [With Joining Bonus]', '/en/job/493320/port-supervisor-assistant-port-executive-warehouse-freight-with-joining-bonus', 'Operations', '2023-12-31 07:55:00', 'O\' Level, NITEC or Diploma in Logistics/ Supply Chain Management. Other disciplines with experience in logistics operations management preferable in 3rd party logistics, distribution or manufacturing environment will also be considered. \nProficiency in MS Excel\nAbility to work independently \nGood communication skills\nWilling to work on a 5.5 days work schedule'),
	(928, 'Cyber Security Network Engineer', '/en/job/493388/cyber-security-network-engineer', 'Infocomm Technology', '2023-10-31 07:55:00', ' Possess a bachelor  degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, or equivalent At least 2 years of relevant experience  Expertise across a variety of security products such as understanding of network    infrastructure, Secure Web Gateway, high volumes of network & data (e.g. Netflow, FPC),    and other attack artifacts in support of incident investigations. Proficiency with any of the following: IDPS, Network Packet Capture, Network Forensics,    Web Application Firewall and DNS security. Advanced understanding of TCP/IP, common networking ports and protocols, traffic flow,    system administration, OSI model, defense-in-depth and common security elements.'),
	(929, 'Identity and Access Management (IAM) Engineer', '/en/job/493390/identity-and-access-management-iam-engineer', 'Infocomm Technology', '2023-10-31 07:55:00', 'Possess a bachelor degree in IT, Information Security, Computer science, or a related field\nAt least 2 years of relevant experience\nWorking knowledge and experience with authentication standards and technologies such as multi factor authentication etc.\nWell-verse with hands-on knowledge of identity and access management best practices, procedures, and software solutions such as IAM, PAM, MFA, etc\nPrior experience with Windows, Lunix, AD and LDAP would be preferred'),
	(930, 'Deputy SOC Manager', '/en/job/493384/deputy-soc-manager', 'Infocomm Technology', '2023-09-30 07:55:00', 'Possess a diploma/degree in Information Systems, Cybersecurity or related disciplines\nMinimum 3 years experience in enterprise SOC operations, security consultancy or security operation\nHands-on experience on SIEM and/or SOAR will be preferred\nGood interpersonal and presentation skills\nA strong team player.\nApplicants with security certifications like GCIH and CISSP will have an added advantage'),
